This paper focuses on the optimization of energy efficiency in robotic movements, specifically through the exploitation of variable physical impedance. This topic falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and involves the use of both optimal control and reinforcement learning, which are subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The hierarchical approach used in the paper also involves system dynamics and control (cs.SY) and mechanical engineering (cs.ME).
